cons:
Very hierarchical culture which explicitly and implicitly curb autonomy;
Terrible hours (they are both long and intense), more than the average of the industry in my region (colleagues from Mck and BCG all agree I have the worst hours of all);
Projects are way understaffed (literally all my projects had people “on top” because the price we charged from the client is too low for the scope agreed; my current project has THREE TIMES the amount of people agreed with the client and even then I’m working 85 hours a week);
Only one way to be: Bain says they are focused on diversity but no profile is accepted other than the typical consutant - highly extrovert, absolute great at analysis, over deliverer (even at the costs of people satisfaction and even when the client was perfectly satisfied and happy with what we had initially agreed on).
Pressure, pressure and pressure (the number of people on mental health leaves is absurd and has quadrupled in the last 2 years);
